Kamarudeen Ogundele, Abuja Bayelsa State Governor, Senator Douye Diri, and his deputy, Senator Lawrence Ewhrudjakpo, have asked the Court of Appeal, Abuja, to join them as defendants in an appeal filed by the Action Peoples Party. APP is challenging the Independent National Electoral Commission over the exclusion of its candidates from the 2019 governorship election in Bayelsa and Kogi States. Their political party, the Peoples Democratic Party, had equally filed an application for joinder. Meanwhile, the court had ordered parties to the appeal to file their written response to the motions for joinder within 24 hours beginning from Wednesday. Copyright PUNCH.
